    <div id="artwork-details">
    <div id="tombstone">

    <p>    Irving Penn<br />
American, 1917–2009<br />
    </p>
    <h3><em>Father and Son with Eggs, Cuzco</em>, 1948, printed May 1978</h3>

    <p>
    Platinum-palladium print, edition 4/14<br />    30 x 28.9 cm (image); 57 x 36.2 cm (paper)<br />    Inscribed verso: “1726 / .. [in a circle]”; inscribed verso: “FATHER AND SON WITH EGGS [underlined] (CUZCO)”; inscribed verso: “BF Paper on Aluminum / Platinum-Palladium / Print made May 1978”; stamped verso: “Deacidified”; inscribed verso: “4/14”; signed and stamped verso: “Irving Penn / Hand-coated by the photographer [in a circle]”; stamped and inscribed verso: “PHOTOGRAPH BY IRVING PENN / Copyright © 1978 by IRVING PENN / Not to be reproduced without / written permission of the / photographer, and / The Conde Nast Publications, Inc.”; stamped and inscribed verso: “In addition to 14 prints of this / image in platinum metals, unnumbered, but signed, silver prints not exceeding 0 may exist.”<br />    Gift of Irving Penn, 1996.258</p>
        Copyright The Irving Penn Foundation
        <!--<p id="dept-gallery">--><!--<br />-->
         <!--</p>-->
    </p>
    </div><!--/tombstone-->

  </div>
  <!--/artwork-details-->

    
      <div id="artwork-body">
                <div id="abbrev">
      <p><a href="http://www.artic.edu//aic/collections/exhibitions/IrvingPennArchives/artwork/more" class="more">Exhibition, Publication and Ownership Histories</a></p>
      <!--content hidden-->
    </div>
    <div id="extended">
      <p><a href="http://www.artic.edu//aic/collections/exhibitions/IrvingPennArchives/artwork/less" class="less">Exhibition, Publication and Ownership Histories</a></p>
            <h2>Exhibition History</h2>
      <p>Chicago, Art Institute of Chicago, “Irving Penn, A Career in Photography,” November 22, 1997–February 1, 1998; traveled to St. Petersburg, Russia, State Hermitage Museum, March 1–May 16, 1998; Hamburg, Germany, Deichtorhallen, June 18–September 6, 1998; Munich, Germany, Müchner Stadtmuseum, October 6, 1998–February 21, 1999; San Francisco, California, Friends of Photography/Ansel Adams Center for Photography, November 11, 1999–January 23, 2000; Museum of Fine Arts, Houston, March 25–June 4, 2000; Paris, France, Maison Européenne de la Photographie, September 13–November 5, 2000. (Colin Westerbeck)<br />
<br />
Chicago, Art Institute of Chicago, "Far from Home: Photography, Travel, and Inspiration," January 20–May 6, 2007. (Elizabeth Siegel and Newell G. Smith)</p>
                  <h2>Publication History</h2>
      <p>Liberman, Alexander. 1951. “The Art and Technique of Color Photography.” Simon and Schuster. p. 11, cat. 11. (other print of this image/variant in color)<br />
<br />
Penn, Irving. 1960. “Moments Preserved.” Simon and Schuster. p. 95. (other print of this image/variant in color)<br />
<br />
Penn, Irving. 1991. “Passage: A Work Record.” Knopf. p. 63. (other print of this image)<br />
<br />
Photology. 1992. “Irving Penn: People in Passage.” Photology. p. 81. (other print of this image)<br />
<br />
Westerbeck, Colin. 1997. “Irving Penn: A Career in Photography.” Exh. cat. Art Institute of Chicago/Bulfinch Press. p. 113, cat. 38, pl. 63.<br />
<br />
Greenough, Sarah. 2005. “Irving Penn: Platinum Prints.” Exh. cat. National Gallery of Art/Yale University Press. pl. 11. (other print of this image)</p>
                  <h2>Ownership History</h2>
      <p>Given by the artist to the Art Institute, 1996.</p>
